Package: bcall
Type: Package
Title: B-Call Analysis for Legislative Voting Data
Version: 1.0.0
Author: B-Call Team
Maintainer: B-Call Team <bcall@example.com>
Description: Implements B-Call methodology for analyzing legislative voting data,
    integrating ideological position (d1) and political cohesion (d2) measurements.
    Provides two main approaches: automatic clustering of legislators or user-provided
    clustering. Users provide data as R data.frames with legislators as rows and votes
    as columns. Includes visualization tools and synthetic data for examples.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    R6 (>= 2.4.0),
    dplyr (>= 1.0.0),
    ggplot2 (>= 3.3.0),
    plotly (>= 4.9.0),
    tidyr (>= 1.1.0),
    tools,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
